---
import Docs from "../layouts/Docs.astro";
---
<Docs title="Specline — honest pitch">
  <div class="doc-kicker">Specline</div>
  <h1>Honest pitch</h1>
  <p class="doc-lead">
    Every promise Specline makes, with the condition under which it breaks. A claim without
    a failure mode is marketing — so here are the failure modes.
  </p>
  <div class="tbl-wrap">
    <table class="book-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Claim</th><th>Mechanism</th><th>Fails when</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Consistent structure, every feature</td><td>One fixed folder shape, checked by Specline</td><td>You skip the checker — then it's a convention again</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rework caught at the cheapest moment</td><td>Acceptance checks run inside the work, not at a demo</td><td>Checks are written unfalsifiably</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Memory that survives staff &amp; models</td><td>Graduation writes knowledge; archive preserves contracts</td><td>Graduation is skipped</td></tr>
        <tr><td>An agent can plan with you, not just code</td><td>The methodology is served to the agent as a tool</td><td>The repo never carries the brief, so the agent isn't aware</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Audit trail</td><td>Every shipped feature resolves to an archived spec</td><td>Archive integrity breaks — a Specline error</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><span class="ci">▲</span><p>What it does <em>not</em> claim: that structure substitutes for product judgment. The system concentrates judgment at two gates and automates everything between.</p></div>
</Docs>
